{"id":"2105.02924","submitter":"Ignacio Araya","authors":"Giorgos Anastasiou, Ignacio J. Araya, Cristobal Corral and Rodrigo\n  Olea","title":"Noether-Wald charges in six-dimensional Critical Gravity","comments":"16 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1007/JHEP07(2021)156","report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th gr-qc","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  It has been recently shown that there is a particular combination of\nconformal invariants in six dimensions which accepts a generic Einstein space\nas a solution. The Lagrangian of this Conformal Gravity theory -- originally\nfound by Lu, Pang and Pope (LPP) -- can be conveniently rewritten in terms of\nproducts and covariant derivatives of the Weyl tensor. This allows one to\nderive the corresponding Noether prepotential and Noether-Wald charges in a\ncompact form. Based on this expression, we calculate the Noether-Wald charges\nof six-dimensional Critical Gravity at the bicritical point, which is defined\nby the difference of the actions for Einstein-AdS gravity and the LPP Conformal\nGravity. When considering Einstein manifolds, we show the vanishing of the\nNoether prepotential of Critical Gravity explicitly, which implies the\ntriviality of the Noether-Wald charges. This result shows the equivalence\nbetween Einstein-AdS gravity and Conformal Gravity within its Einstein sector\nnot only at the level of the action but also at the level of the charges.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 May 2021 19:36:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-04"}
